nsistency. The proposed framework significantly improves upon existing DUN-based models by introducing interpretable geometric constraints rooted in both linear algebra and manifold learning, offering superior robustness to undersampling and noise. If successful, this work will set a new standard for consistent, high-fidelity multi-contrast MRI reconstruction with direct implications for clinical diagnosis, longitudinal studies, and quantitative imaging.",
